The paper discusses scholarly information-seeking behavior and the use of academic social networks, which are relevant to the fields of information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The study also examines differences between researchers according to discipline, which could fall under social and information sciences (cs.SI) or cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses implications for the design of research platforms, which could be relevant to the field of social computing (cs.SOC).
